In this level, the password for the next level is obtained from a cron job that runs periodically.

Login to Bandit Level 21 using SSH:ssh bandit21@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
After login, the current working directory is the home directory of bandit21.
->List the cron job directory:ls /etc/cron.d
A cron job file named cronjob_bandit22 is present.
View the contents of the cron job file:
->cat /etc/cron.d/cronjob_bandit22
The cron job executes a script periodically.
View the script to find where the password is stored:
-> cat /usr/bin/cronjob_bandit22.sh
The script writes the password to a temporary file.
Read the temporary file:
->cat /tmp/tRae0UfB9v0UzbCdn9cY0gQnds9GF58Q


->Password for Level 22:tRae0UfB9v0UzbCdn9cY0gQnds9GF58Q
